[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcom.example.TikaAppUnpackerFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1m([0mTikaAppUnpackerFuzzer.jav[1;92ma:54[0m[1m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         DEDUP_TOKEN: ea76e639355e804b                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         == libFuzzer crashing input ==                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mReport[0m===                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         A FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical exception was raised by the Jazzer FilePathTraversal  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         sanitizer, indicating a file path traversal vulnerability. The sanitizer detected   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         that a file output path [1m([0m`[35m/tmp/[0m[95mexpander-tmp[0m…[35m/q/r/s/t/../../[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m`[1m)[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         included upward traversal [1m([0m`..`[1m)[0m outside the expected directory. The issue was      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         triggered during processing of embedded documents in Apache Tika via the TikaCLI    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         harness.                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Issue Nature                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           The issue is a file path traversal vulnerability detected at runtime by Jazzer’s  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         FilePathTraversal sanitizer. An input to the fuzzer caused the code to attempt to   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         write or extract a file to a path containing `..[35m/[0m` segments, allowing it to escape  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         the intended output directory.                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Vulnerability Type                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           File path traversal [1m([0malso known as directory traversal[1m)[0m, where attackers can      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         manipulate file paths to access or create files outside of a designated directory.  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Key Observations                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • The exception originates in                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `com.code_intelligence.jazzer.sanitizers.FilePathTraversal.check` and propagates    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         through `checkFile`, `checkObj`, and `processFileOutputStartHook`.                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • The vulnerable code path is exercised by Tika’s embedded document extractor     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m([0m`TikaCLI$FileEmbeddedDocumentExtractor.parseEmbedded`[1m)[0m.                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • The stack trace continues through `PackageParser.parseEntry` and                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `CompositeParser.parse` before reaching the user’s fuzzer harness                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m([0m`TikaAppUnpackerFuzzer`[1m)[0m.                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • The harness merely feeds inputs to Tika; it is not the root cause but serves as [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         the entry point for this test case.                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Areas for Investigation                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m1[0m. FilePathTraversal sanitizer implementation [1m([0mespecially `checkFile` and         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `processFileOutputStartHook`[1m)[0m to understand path normalization and checks.          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m2[0m. Tika’s EmbeddedDocumentExtractor logic in                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `TikaCLI$FileEmbeddedDocumentExtractor.parseEmbedded` for how output paths are      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         constructed.                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m3[0m. PackageParser’s handling of archive entries and any path sanitization applied  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         before extraction.                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m4[0m. Overall file output workflow in TikaCLI to identify where traversal checks     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         should occur and how paths are validated.                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         By reviewing these components, one can build a comprehensive view of how upward     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         path traversal slips through and at which stage stricter validation may be          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         required.                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Initial Issue Log                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Here is the initial issue log of the codebase:                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m<[0m[1;95missue[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         A Jazzer-based fuzz test reported a critical File Path Traversal issue when Apache  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Tika’s CLI unpacker writes extracted files. The initial exception originates in     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `FilePathTraversal.check` and surfaces while TikaCLI processes embedded documents.  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         A patch was proposed in `TikaCLI.java` to validate canonical paths—comparing the    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         output file’s canonical path against the extraction directory’s canonical path and  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         throwing an `IOException` on mismatch. After applying this change, the build fails  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         with compilation errors: calls to `[1;35mgetCanonicalPath[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` and the thrown `IOException` [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         are neither caught nor declared in the method’s signature.                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. Initial Issue                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Exception:                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              `com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: File path       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         traversal: [35m/tmp/[0m…[35m/[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m`                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Stack trace points to:                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              - `FilePathTraversal.check*` in Jazzer’s sanitizer                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              - `TikaCLI$[1;35mFileEmbeddedDocumentExtractor.parseEmbedded[0m[1m([0mTikaCLI.jav[1;92ma:1111[0m[1m)[0m`     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              - Further parsing in `PackageParser`, `CompositeParser`, etc., invoked from    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `TikaCLI.main` and the user’s fuzzer harness.                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Observation: The fuzzer supplied a path containing `…[35m/[0m…[35m/[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m`,     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         leading to traversal outside the intended extraction directory.                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. Patch Attempt                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - File: `tika-app/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/cli/TikaCLI.java`                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Location: Inside the block that determines `outputFile = new [1;35mFile[0m[1m([0mextractDir,  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         normalizedName[1m)[0m` before writing content.                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Added code:                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              ```                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              [35m/[0m[35m/[0m Prevent directory traversal by validating canonical paths                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              String canonicalExtractDir = [1;35mextractDir.getCanonicalPath[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m;                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              String canonicalOutputPath = [1;35moutputFile.getCanonicalPath[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m;                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              if [1m([0m![1;35mcanonicalOutputPath.startsWith[0m[1m([0mcanonicalExtractDir + File.separator[1m)[0m[1m)[0m [1m{[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                  throw new [1;35mIOException[0m[1m([0m[32m"Invalid file name [0m[32m([0m[32mpath traversal[0m[32m)[0m[32m: "[0m +             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         normalizedName[1m)[0m;                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              [1m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              ```                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Purpose: Ensure `normalizedName` does not escape `extractDir`.                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. Patch Result                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Build failure in the `tika-app` module:                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              ```                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              unreported exception java.io.IOException; must be caught or declared to be     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         thrown                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              ```                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Errors at lines where:                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              - `[1;35mextractDir.getCanonicalPath[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`                                              [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m            - Root compilation issue: the enclosing method neither catches these             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `IOException`s nor declares them in its `throws` clause.                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m. Further Investigation                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Inspect the signature of the method containing the patched block [1m([0mlikely       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `parseEmbedded` or its caller[1m)[0m to see how I/O errors are handled or declared.       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Review adjacent code paths in `TikaCLI$FileEmbeddedDocumentExtractor` and any  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         overriding or callback methods for existing exception-handling patterns.            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Survey other file-output hooks in the Tika CLI [1m([0me.g., streaming or temp-file   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         logic[1m)[0m to ensure a consistent exception model around file operations and to detect  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1090[0m[39m:        @Override[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1091[0m[39m:        public void [0m[1;35mparseEmbedded[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTikaInputStream tis, ContentHandler [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontentHandler, Metadata metadata, boolean outputHtml[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws SAXException, [0m        [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1092[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The new directory-traversal sanity check invokes two methods that declare [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`throws IOException`:  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `[0m[1;35mFile.getCanonicalPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` itself.  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Those calls live inside the helper method `[0m[1;35mgetOutputFile[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, which [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moriginally did *not* declare any checked exceptions.  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Meanwhile, the only caller of `getOutputFile` is `[0m[1;35mparseEmbedded[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, which [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39malready declares `throws IOException`.  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Patch Outline  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Reapply the canonical-path checks exactly as in the last patch attempt, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m*inside* `getOutputFile`, so you centralize all filename-normalization and security[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecks in one place.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. Modify the signature of `getOutputFile` to declare `throws IOException`.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Change:  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```java[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m before[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        private File [0m[1;35mgetOutputFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString name, Metadata metadata, MediaType [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontentType[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[33m...[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        to  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```java[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m after[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        private File [0m[1;35mgetOutputFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString name,[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                                   Metadata metadata,[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                                   MediaType contentType[0m[1;39m)[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                                   throws IOException [0m[1;39m{[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[33m...[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. Verify that the import for `java.io.IOException` is present at the top of the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfile [0m[1;39m([0m[39mit already is, thanks to `parseEmbedded` throwing it[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   D. No other callers of `getOutputFile` exist; `[0m[1;35mparseEmbedded[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` will [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mautomatically propagate the exception.  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   E. Recompile and run existing tests and the CLI to ensure nothing else breaks.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Why This Works  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By declaring `throws IOException` on `getOutputFile`, all internal calls to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mgetCanonicalPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and the explicit `throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` become properly [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeclared.  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mparseEmbedded[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` already lists `throws IOException`, so no downstream [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msignature changes are required.  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We preserve the existing exception-handling in the “save‐file” block: any I/O [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39merrors *during* copy remain caught by the original `catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mException e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` around the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FileOutputStream`, and are logged as warnings.  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The new path-traversal check aborts extraction only at the *filename* phase, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msurfacing a clear error rather than silently writing outside the target directory. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Preservation of Existing Logic and Compatibility  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The file-naming, normalization, UUID-prefix logic, parent-dir creation, and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwrite loop remain untouched.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We do *not* alter the harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39mJazzer fuzz code[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, CLI argument parsing, or any[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtest code.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - CLI behavior on a bad embedded name is still to throw `IOException` out of [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`parseEmbedded`. The overall `TikaCLI.main` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor its caller[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m may exit with an error,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhich is acceptable: a hazardous extraction is explicitly rejected.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No external libraries or utility functions are modified.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Side-Effects and Mitigation  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Side Effect: If a malicious/buggy embedded name is detected, the CLI will [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mabort processing that document [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand likely exit[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. If we later decide to *skip* only[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe bad entry and continue with others, we could catch the `IOException` in [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`parseEmbedded` and log a warning [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmatching the downstream I/O catch[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. For now, the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstrict failure aligns with a “critical security issue” policy.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Mitigation: For more graceful degradation, wrap the `[0m[1;35mgetOutputFile[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` call [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min a `try`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mIOException e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` inside `parseEmbedded`, log a warning, and then [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`return;` to continue with the next embedded resource.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Steps to Implement  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. In `tika-app/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/cli/TikaCLI.java`, locate the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhelper method:  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```java[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      private File [0m[1;35mgetOutputFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString name,[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                                 Metadata metadata,[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                                 MediaType contentType[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Change its signature to:  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```java[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      private File [0m[1;35mgetOutputFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString name,[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                                 Metadata metadata,[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                                 MediaType contentType[0m[1;39m)[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                                 throws IOException [0m[1;39m{[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Ensure the canonical-path check code is present inside that method, [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimmediately after `new [0m[1;35mFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mextractDir, normalizedName[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`:  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```java[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      String canonicalExtractDir   = [0m[1;35mextractDir.getCanonicalPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      String canonicalOutputPath   = [0m[1;35moutputFile.getCanonicalPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mcanonicalOutputPath.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcanonicalExtractDir + File.separator[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Invalid file name [0m[32m([0m[32mpath traversal[0m[32m)[0m[32m: "[0m[39m + [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnormalizedName[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Save, recompile [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`mvn clean install`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and verify that the three compilation [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39merrors disappear and that the CLI still behaves as expected on valid inputs.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
